# React Hook Form 7

Use React Hook Form for any form with more than 2 inputs or with cross-field validation. Pair with the Zod schemas defined in `src/features/<feature>/schemas.ts`.

## Setup

Install the Zod resolver (one-time): `pnpm --filter @darchive/web add @hookform/resolvers`.

```tsx
"use client";
import { useForm } from "react-hook-form";
import { zodResolver } from "@hookform/resolvers/zod";
import { guestbookCreateInputSchema, type GuestbookCreateInput } from "../schemas";

export function GuestbookForm() {
  const form = useForm<GuestbookCreateInput>({
    resolver: zodResolver(guestbookCreateInputSchema),
    defaultValues: { name: "", message: "" },
  });

  const onSubmit = form.handleSubmit(async (values) => {
    await createMutation.mutateAsync(values);
    form.reset();
  });

  return (
    <form onSubmit={onSubmit}>
      <input {...form.register("name")} maxLength={40} />
      {form.formState.errors.name ? <p>{form.formState.errors.name.message}</p> : null}
      <textarea {...form.register("message")} maxLength={500} />
      <button type="submit" disabled={form.formState.isSubmitting}>Send</button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Controller for Non-Native Inputs

Use `<Controller>` for Radix/MUI/custom controlled inputs (Select, Switch, DatePicker, etc.):

```tsx
import { Controller } from "react-hook-form";

<Controller
  control={form.control}
  name="attendance"
  render={({ field }) => (
    <RadioGroup value={field.value} onValueChange={field.onChange}>{/* ... */}</RadioGroup>
  )}
/>
```

## Rules

- One Zod schema per form, reused on the server (tRPC `.input(...)`) and the client (`zodResolver`).
- Read submit state from `form.formState.isSubmitting` (not custom state).
- Do NOT manually call `safeParse` inside `onSubmit` — the resolver does it.
- Use `form.reset()` after successful submission instead of resetting individual fields.
- Avoid `useState` for form fields — that's what RHF replaces.
- For optimistic UI, call `mutation.mutate(values)` and `form.reset()` in the same tick; rely on TanStack Query for rollback.

## When to Skip RHF

For a single-field input (search box, toggle), `useState` is fine. Don't pull in RHF for trivial state.
